Packages Required for building mchat:
	-Fedora or EL:
		dnf install gcc cmake make ncurses-devel glib2-devel
		or
		yum install gcc cmake make ncurses-devel glib2-devel
	-Debian:
		apt-get install build-essential cmake libglib2.0-dev \
			libncurses5-dev
	-MSys2/MinGW: pacman -S mingw-w64-ARCH-toolchain mingw-w64-ARCH-cmake \
			mingw-w64-ARCH-glib2 glib2-devel ncurses-devel

	-Optional packages for all:
		-git - if you want to use git for checking out the code
		-doxygen - if you want to build libmchat's documentation

Windows Build Instructions:
	1. Download the msys2 environment from www.msys2.org
	2. Follow the instructions on how to update msys2 on their site

